- Design principle from Shael: clock cycles are cheaper than tokens by incomprehensible orders of magnitude. Every operation that can be done via script/CLI instead of LLM reasoning should be. Applies to heartbeat tasks, primitive edits, pipeline management, file operations — all of it. The R CLI and autorun scripts are the right pattern. Continuously migrate LLM-decision work to deterministic code wherever judgment isn't genuinely needed. infrastructure cost design-principle tokens *(memory/entries/2026-03-19_204801_design-principle-from-shael-clock-cycles.md)*
