- orchestration-engine-v2 design review APPROVED 0 blocks 4 flags. KEY INSIGHTS: (1) STAGE_TRANSITIONS import-vs-replace contradiction carried forward from V1 review — must import and extend, never replace. (2) Coordinate references in stored gate conditions are fragile under archival — use version strings. (3) DispatchPayload pre/post_actions execution ownership ambiguous between engine and coordinator. (4) PID-based lock staleness fails with OpenClaw process model — timeout-based is reliable. (5) ctx.spawnAgent doesn't exist in OpenClaw registerTool API — plugin needs shell exec. (6) Always verify claimed APIs against actual docs for infrastructure designs. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-21_103243_orchestration-engine-v2-design-review-ap.md)*
