- Supervised builder experiment runner works. Key changes: (1) run_experiment.py rewritten — default mode spawns builder agent to own entire experiment lifecycle (read notebook, create standalone runner, execute, fix bugs, create primitives, report completion). --direct flag for unsupervised fallback. (2) Root cause of stack-specialists and validate-scheme-b failures: papermill detection bug (subprocess.run doesn't raise on non-zero exit, was setting papermill_available=True incorrectly) + builder recovery used wrong CLI syntax (openclaw gateway sessions send --agent doesn't exist, correct is openclaw agent --agent). (3) Fixed RESULTS_BASE missing from pipeline_autorun.py, added all local analysis stages to agent_actions sets, added failed experiment retry detection. (4) Convention: experiments always run through supervised builder by default — builder creates run_supervised.py, executes, fixes bugs inline, creates primitives for findings. infrastructure experiments builder supervised-runner *(memory/entries/2026-03-19_191633_supervised-builder-experiment-runner-wor.md)*
- Design principle from Shael: clock cycles are cheaper than tokens by incomprehensible orders of magnitude. Every operation that can be done via script/CLI instead of LLM reasoning should be. Applies to heartbeat tasks, primitive edits, pipeline management, file operations — all of it. The R CLI and autorun scripts are the right pattern. Continuously migrate LLM-decision work to deterministic code wherever judgment isn't genuinely needed. infrastructure cost design-principle tokens *(memory/entries/2026-03-19_204801_design-principle-from-shael-clock-cycles.md)*
- Session 2026-03-19 20:42-20:50 UTC — Shael review of pipeline results. Sent all 3 PDF analysis reports (build-equilibrium-snn, stack-specialists, validate-scheme-b). Key decisions: (1) Versioning: the three concurrent pipelines are V5 Phase 1 iterations (v5-equilibrium, v5-stacking, v5-validation). The convergence proposal (phasic-dominant + Scheme B) is V6 Phase 1, not Phase 3. Updated all 6 primitives via R edit. (2) V6 proposal set to pending_review awaiting Shael approval. (3) Reinforced design principle: clock cycles >> tokens — always prefer scripts/CLI over LLM reasoning for deterministic work. (4) Shael happy with autonomous operation — let pipelines run, ping only when something needs human eyes. session v5 v6 versioning reports *(memory/entries/2026-03-19_205031_session-2026-03-19-2042-2050-utc-shael-r.md)*
