- Codex Engine design locked with Shael. Unified primitive nav/edit/view system replacing all separate R commands. One command, five modes (view implicit, -e edit, -g graph, -x execute, -n create). Namespace: p=pipelines, w=workspaces, t=tasks, d=decisions, l=lessons, c=commands, k=knowledge, s=skills, m=memory. Field-indexed editing with cascading consequences, render diffs, undo stack. V1 scope: core engine + mutations + graph + execute + create. V2: undo, dry-run, boot hook. Task: tasks/build-codex-engine.md --tags codex-engine,infrastructure,design,milestone *(memory/entries/2026-03-20_174427_codex-engine-design-locked-with-shael-un.md)*
