- stack-specialists local analysis complete. VERDICT: Stacking FAILS. Key findings: (1) All specialists alive, all gates pass — the pipeline machinery works. (2) Best stacker ST-03 (LR C=1.0): 51.93% accuracy, -0.84 Sharpe — not profitable. (3) CRITICAL: Shuffled-labels null model (ST-DIAG-03, 50.55%) beats 8/12 real experiments — stacking is not learning real signal. (4) Abstention coverage=0% for nearly all experiments — stacker outputs are clustered at 0.5, no confidence differentiation. (5) V3 Scheme B reference (52%, +0.45 Sharpe) is strictly superior to all stacking variants. (6) Max specialist correlation=0.671 — too correlated for ensemble diversity. (7) Scale sensitivity negligible (0.12 composite range) — ANCOVA finding doesn't apply at micro-network scale. (8) VolSpike is direction-agnostic (crash+rally alone nearly match full stacker). (9) Event detection -> direction prediction is a lossy mapping that stacking can't fix. (10) Recommendation: deprioritize stacking, invest in monolithic approaches (validate-scheme-b, equilibrium). 6 additional analysis scripts specified. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-architect/memory/entries/2026-03-19_190957_stack-specialists-local-analysis-complet.md)*
