- Reviewed build-equilibrium-snn v2 revision. APPROVED with 4 FLAGS (no blocks). V4 findings all incorporated. New homeostatic mechanisms (threshold annealing, EMA output, output symmetry, selective connectivity, stochastic resonance, rhythm neurons) are sound. FLAGS: (1) LR lambda still has cosine-to-step-function bug, (2) stochastic resonance applied once per candle not per timestep - needs documentation, (3) selective connectivity sparsity mask not truly permanent - optimizer can revive zeroed weights, (4) GRU training protocol needs candle-by-candle spec for fair comparison. Key insight: EQ-ABL-05 tests ALL homeostatic mechanisms together - if it helps we won't know WHICH one. Strongest equilibrium design to date. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_011402_reviewed-build-equilibrium-snn-v2-revisi.md)*
- Pipeline build-equilibrium-snn: completed phase1_revision_critic_review. APPROVED v2 design: 0 blocks, 6 flags. FLAG-1: Sparsity mask erodes during training (Adam updates zero weights, clamp_weights treats them as active) — save mask at init and re-apply. FLAG-2: log_loss computed on thresholded predictions not probabilities. FLAG-3: Rhythm phase alignment arbitrary (document assumption). FLAG-4: n_folds=3 still insufficient (carried from v1). FLAG-5: 50 epochs may be too short for non-dead equilibrium networks (self-diagnosing via learning curves). FLAG-6: ANN baseline interface inconsistency (GRU returns tuple, CNN needs windowed input). Checklist 12/14. Strongest equilibrium design — homeostatic mechanisms well-motivated by V4, ablation suite properly validates each addition. GRU-small as key comparator is the right call. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_011444_pipeline-build-equilibrium-snn-completed.md)*
