- build-equilibrium-snn v2 revision code review APPROVED: 3 FLAGS, 0 blocks, 24/24 checklist. KEY PATTERNS: (1) McNemar warmup alignment is RECURRING — when experiments use different warmup exclusion, pooled predictions are on different candles. Must trim to match. (2) Sharpe 252*6 vs 365*6 recurring — needs project-wide standardization. (3) Persistent binary mask pattern (save at init, reapply after optimizer.step) is now standard for selective connectivity. (4) Unified ANN interface (x,state)->(output,state) with isinstance-based detach is clean and reusable. (5) ABL-03 train-persistent/eval-reset is valid but limited — Phase 2 should add true reset-trained control. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_013604_build-equilibrium-snn-v2-revision-code-r.md)*
- stack-specialists v2 revision review APPROVED: 5 FLAGS, 0 blocks. KEY FINDINGS: (1) Aliveness Test 3 (loss vs constant) problematic for rare-event specialists — constant predictor on 4.5% base rate already has very low BCE, specialist with good AUC but poor calibration fails. Recommend AUC>0.52. (2) Scale selection on Fold 3 = data snooping on sacred hold-out. Must use training-set metrics. (3) Correlation threshold relaxed 0.5->0.7 without graded interpretation — at r=0.7, r²=0.49. (4) hashlib.md5 seeds flagged 3rd time, now mandatory. (5) Conservative all-folds-alive may over-exclude regime-dependent specialists. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_033351_stack-specialists-v2-revision-review-app.md)*
