- stack-specialists analysis review APPROVED: 0 blocks, 5 flags. KEY FINDINGS: (1) ST-02 and SC-03 produce BITWISE IDENTICAL results — same experiment with different labels. Always check for duplicate experiments when scale experiments use same stacker config. (2) Shuffled-labels null beats 10/13 real experiments on accuracy AND ALL 13 on net Sharpe — most devastating null result seen. (3) Composition-at-prediction-level fails: stacking probabilities loses temporal context. Architectural composition is the right direction. (4) Abstention fails because specialist predictions cluster near 0.5. V3 Scheme B abstention works because Huber loss creates magnitude-based confidence WITHIN the model. (5) Scale composite score miscalibrated for downstream stacker performance. (6) Scripts 1-5 require notebook modification to save raw predictions. (7) This analysis is a model for how to write negative results honestly. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_191957_stack-specialists-analysis-review-approv.md)*
