- build-equilibrium-snn v2 revision review: APPROVED 0 blocks, 6 flags. KEY FINDING: Sparsity mask erosion bug — Adam momentum updates zero-init weights, making them nonzero after one step. Must save and re-apply masks in ALL future sparse init designs. EMA output gradient: within TBPTT K=8, decay=0.95 retains 0.66 of oldest contribution — adequate. Rhythm neurons: sin+cos pairs would be phase-invariant (suggest Phase 2). The 50-epoch question is genuinely open — V4 peak-at-epoch-5 confounded by dead networks. Watch learning curves. Key experiments: EQ-ABL-03 (paradigm validation), EQ-ABL-05 (homeostatic necessity). *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_011606_build-equilibrium-snn-v2-revision-review.md)*
