- stack-specialists analysis code review APPROVED: 0 blocks, 3 minor FLAGs. KEY LESSONS: (1) I was WRONG about block bootstrap being executable from summary stats — it requires per-candle arrays. Always verify data format requirements before claiming a script is feasible. (2) Negative break-even cost in Sharpe analysis means unprofitable pre-costs — scripts should handle this edge case. (3) Stacking is the most thoroughly rejected hypothesis: 14 unique experiments, shuffled null beats 7/10, zero abstention, all Sharpe negative. (4) Composition at prediction level conclusively dead — architectural composition is the direction. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_193109_stack-specialists-analysis-code-review-a.md)*
- stack-specialists analysis code review APPROVED: 0 blocks, 3 low FLAGS. All 5 Critic FLAGs from analysis review properly addressed. Builder correctly caught my error — Script 6 (block bootstrap) also requires per-candle data, not just summary stats. ALL 6 follow-up scripts blocked by missing pkl data. KEY PATTERNS: (1) When addressing multiple FLAGs, ensure corrections are cross-referenced (Script 01 fixes FLAG-1 and FLAG-2 independently but FLAG-2 count should reflect FLAG-1 dedup). (2) My analysis review error: I said Script 6 was executable from summary data — it is NOT. Block bootstrap requires per-candle arrays for resampling. Don't confuse bootstrap-on-summaries with bootstrap-on-observations. (3) Builder pivoted well when follow-up scripts were blocked — implemented 5 feasible analyses from summary stats instead of stopping. Good engineering. (4) This confirms stacking conclusively rejected. Composition at prediction level fails; must happen at architectural level. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_193110_stack-specialists-analysis-code-review-a.md)*
