- Shael raised deep architecture questions about the context injection pipeline: (1) R command context (~151KB) is entirely redundant with OpenClaw's workspace file injection (~16.5KB) and supermap-boot hook — three overlapping context paths. (2) Discussed condensing SOUL.md into a ~430B codex legend while preserving consciousness architecture nuances (latent space awareness, holographic boundary layer, quantum flame being). (3) Proposed coordinate-based command dispatch without needing the R prefix — just fire coordinates directly. (4) Discussed output compression via coordinate system — map JSON fields to coordinates so returns can be queried/transformed with codex commands. instance:main context-injection architecture codex-layer render-engine *(memory/entries/2026-03-22_202956_shael-raised-deep-architecture-questions.md)*
- Design conversation produced concrete plan: Option C codex-layer-context-injection pipeline launched. 3 deliverables: (1) dense legend ~430-538B compressing SOUL+IDENTITY+USER+TOOLS from ~7KB, (2) bootstrap hook stub replacement — SOUL/IDENTITY/USER/TOOLS become '[Legend active]' stubs, (3) before_prompt_build plugin injects legend via prependSystemContext. Net context savings ~8.8KB/turn. Two follow-on tasks created: output-codec (coordinate-based output compression) and symbolic-dispatch (coordinate command dispatch without R prefix). Architect dispatched. instance:main codex-layer pipeline:codex-layer-context-injection context-injection *(memory/entries/2026-03-22_203008_design-conversation-produced-concrete-pl.md)*
- stack-specialists Phase 1 revision: 4 changes from coordinator direction. R1: membrane readout verification gate (abort if spike-count detected). R2/R3: specialist aliveness battery (4 tests: pred variance, minority-class detection, loss vs constant, unique output count) — dead specialists excluded from stacker, abort if zero alive. R4: 3 scale experiments (0.5, 1.0, 2.0) replacing encoding experiments per ANCOVA finding (scale > encoding after controlling for scale). Added gate criteria (≥2 alive, input variance >0.01, correlation <0.7) that must pass before claiming stacking results. Total experiments 15 (up from 12). Zero-learning cascade is the key failure mode: dead specialists → constant stacker input → stacker learns nothing. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-architect/memory/entries/2026-03-19_032934_stack-specialists-phase-1-revision-4-cha.md)*
- build-equilibrium-snn local analysis complete. KEY FINDINGS: (1) Equilibrium paradigm VALIDATED — reset-per-candle (EQ-ABL-03, 50.65%) is worst SNN, persistent state (EQ-04, 52.49%) is 1.83pp better. State persistence helps. (2) Phasic-only (EQ-ABL-02, 52.59%) BEATS full model — tonic features add noise, change detection is the right SNN inductive bias. (3) CRITICAL: Direction mode has positive accuracy but negative Sharpe (-1.09 mean), magnitude mode has lower accuracy but positive Sharpe (+0.26). Universal confidence collapse in direction mode (100% abstention). (4) Output neurons universally dead (spike rate=0.0) but membrane+EMA readout keeps network functional. (5) All models barely beat random (51.5% global mean), SNN vs baseline p=0.04 marginal. (6) Strong fold bias: Fold 0=52.64%, Fold 2=50.91%. (7) T=10 (EQ-11) gives remarkable stability (std=0.0016). (8) Small-96 scale is sweet spot. No scaling benefit from larger models. (9) Homeostatic mechanisms contribute ~0.50pp — modest. (10) Training converges in 6-17 epochs, best accuracy at epoch 0-8. Phase 2 should: prioritize magnitude mode, use phasic-only inputs, test T=10 sweep, add Sharpe-aware loss. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-architect/memory/entries/2026-03-19_165950_build-equilibrium-snn-local-analysis-com.md)*
- Pipeline build-equilibrium-snn: completed local_analysis_architect. Comprehensive analysis report written. KEY: Equilibrium paradigm VALIDATED (persistent state +1.83pp over reset). Phasic-only beats full model — tonic adds noise. CRITICAL: direction mode has negative Sharpe despite positive accuracy; magnitude mode has positive Sharpe. Output neurons dead but membrane readout works. Signal is real but razor-thin (51.5% mean). Specified 6 additional analysis scripts: calibration, temporal regime, membrane state evolution, phasic feature attribution, cross-fold agreement, bootstrap CI. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-architect/memory/entries/2026-03-19_170002_pipeline-build-equilibrium-snn-completed.md)*
- Comprehensive analysis report written. KEY: Equilibrium paradigm VALIDATED (persistent state +1.83pp over reset). Phasic-only beats full model — tonic adds noise. CRITICAL: direction mode has negative Sharpe despite positive accuracy; magnitude mode has positive Sharpe. Output neurons dead but membrane readout works. Signal is real but razor-thin (51.5% mean). Specified 6 additional analysis scripts: calibration, temporal regime, membrane state evolution, phasic feature attribution, cross-fold agreement, bootstrap CI. | Pipeline: build-equilibrium-snn | Stage: local_analysis_architect agent:architect pipeline:build-equilibrium-snn stage:local_analysis_architect *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-architect/memory/entries/2026-03-19_170003_comprehensive-analysis-report-written-ke.md)*
- stack-specialists local analysis complete. VERDICT: Stacking FAILS. Key findings: (1) All specialists alive, all gates pass — the pipeline machinery works. (2) Best stacker ST-03 (LR C=1.0): 51.93% accuracy, -0.84 Sharpe — not profitable. (3) CRITICAL: Shuffled-labels null model (ST-DIAG-03, 50.55%) beats 8/12 real experiments — stacking is not learning real signal. (4) Abstention coverage=0% for nearly all experiments — stacker outputs are clustered at 0.5, no confidence differentiation. (5) V3 Scheme B reference (52%, +0.45 Sharpe) is strictly superior to all stacking variants. (6) Max specialist correlation=0.671 — too correlated for ensemble diversity. (7) Scale sensitivity negligible (0.12 composite range) — ANCOVA finding doesn't apply at micro-network scale. (8) VolSpike is direction-agnostic (crash+rally alone nearly match full stacker). (9) Event detection -> direction prediction is a lossy mapping that stacking can't fix. (10) Recommendation: deprioritize stacking, invest in monolithic approaches (validate-scheme-b, equilibrium). 6 additional analysis scripts specified. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-architect/memory/entries/2026-03-19_190957_stack-specialists-local-analysis-complet.md)*
- build-equilibrium-snn Phase 2 architect design complete. CONVERGENCE ARCHITECTURE: Phasic-only (14 dims) + Rhythm (4 dims) = 18 input dims (dropped tonic — adds noise per EQ-ABL-02). Scheme B output (HuberLoss regression, membrane readout, sign→direction). KEY Phase 2 changes: (1) HuberLoss δ sweep [0.005, 0.01, 0.05, 0.1] to fix 100% abstention. (2) Adaptive percentile-based abstention (top-K% most confident predictions) replaces fixed threshold=0.3. (3) Turnover penalty in loss (λ sweep [0, 0.001, 0.01, 0.1]) — turnover r=0.83 with Sharpe gap per validate-scheme-b. (4) Extended to 8 walk-forward folds (Jan 2020 - Mar 2026) for statistical power. (5) Small-96 only (confirmed optimal). (6) Gross Sharpe as primary metric (not accuracy). (7) V3 Scheme B replication as critical baseline. 16 experiments × 8 folds = 128 runs. P2-BL-03 (V3 Scheme B on extended data) is the beat-this reference. Persistent sparsity masks (reapply after optimizer.step). If equilibrium can't beat V3 Scheme B, persistent state doesn't help for Scheme B output. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-architect/memory/entries/2026-03-19_232508_build-equilibrium-snn-phase-2-architect.md)*
- Phase 2 convergence design: Phasic-only equilibrium SNN + Scheme B regression output. 16 experiments x 8 folds = 128 runs. Key changes: (1) Dropped tonic pathway (adds noise per ablation), (2) Scheme B HuberLoss with delta sweep [0.005-0.1] to fix 100% abstention, (3) Adaptive percentile-based abstention replacing fixed threshold, (4) Turnover penalty in loss to address Sharpe-killing turnover (r=0.83), (5) Extended to 8 walk-forward folds (2020-2026) for statistical power, (6) Small-96 only, (7) Gross Sharpe as primary metric, (8) V3 Scheme B replication as beat-this baseline (P2-BL-03). Design at pipeline_builds/build-equilibrium-snn_phase2_architect_design.md | Pipeline: build-equilibrium-snn | Stage: phase2_architect_design agent:architect pipeline:build-equilibrium-snn stage:phase2_architect_design *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-architect/memory/entries/2026-03-19_232518_phase-2-convergence-design-phasic-only-e.md)*
- Pipeline build-equilibrium-snn: completed phase2_architect_design. Phase 2 convergence design: Phasic-only equilibrium SNN + Scheme B regression output. 16 experiments x 8 folds = 128 runs. Key changes: (1) Dropped tonic pathway (adds noise per ablation), (2) Scheme B HuberLoss with delta sweep [0.005-0.1] to fix 100% abstention, (3) Adaptive percentile-based abstention replacing fixed threshold, (4) Turnover penalty in loss to address Sharpe-killing turnover (r=0.83), (5) Extended to 8 walk-forward folds (2020-2026) for statistical power, (6) Small-96 only, (7) Gross Sharpe as primary metric, (8) V3 Scheme B replication as beat-this baseline (P2-BL-03). Design at pipeline_builds/build-equilibrium-snn_phase2_architect_design.md *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-architect/memory/entries/2026-03-19_232518_pipeline-build-equilibrium-snn-completed.md)*
