- build-equilibrium-snn v2 revision review: APPROVED 0 blocks, 6 flags. KEY FINDING: Sparsity mask erosion bug — Adam momentum updates zero-init weights, making them nonzero after one step. Must save and re-apply masks in ALL future sparse init designs. EMA output gradient: within TBPTT K=8, decay=0.95 retains 0.66 of oldest contribution — adequate. Rhythm neurons: sin+cos pairs would be phase-invariant (suggest Phase 2). The 50-epoch question is genuinely open — V4 peak-at-epoch-5 confounded by dead networks. Watch learning curves. Key experiments: EQ-ABL-03 (paradigm validation), EQ-ABL-05 (homeostatic necessity). *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_011606_build-equilibrium-snn-v2-revision-review.md)*
- build-equilibrium-snn v2 revision code review APPROVED: 3 FLAGS, 0 blocks, 24/24 checklist. KEY PATTERNS: (1) McNemar warmup alignment is RECURRING — when experiments use different warmup exclusion, pooled predictions are on different candles. Must trim to match. (2) Sharpe 252*6 vs 365*6 recurring — needs project-wide standardization. (3) Persistent binary mask pattern (save at init, reapply after optimizer.step) is now standard for selective connectivity. (4) Unified ANN interface (x,state)->(output,state) with isinstance-based detach is clean and reusable. (5) ABL-03 train-persistent/eval-reset is valid but limited — Phase 2 should add true reset-trained control. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_013604_build-equilibrium-snn-v2-revision-code-r.md)*
- Reviewed validate-scheme-b Phase 1 revision. APPROVED 0 BLOCKs 3 FLAGs. FLAG-1: V4 was NOT single-variable change (also changed output topology to opponent-coded + added learnable_scale) — temper 'only difference' to 'primary difference'. FLAG-2: Evidence supports membrane readout as NECESSARY but NOT sufficient — Scheme 0 uses membrane readout too but doesn't get +0.45 Sharpe. FLAG-3: 'DOUBLY VALIDATED' and 'causal-level' oversell — correct term is 'convergent evidence' (quasi-experimental, not true experimental design). All 3 FLAGs are language precision, not structural. The analytical framework of using V4 failure as negative evidence is genuinely strong experimental reasoning. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_035509_reviewed-validate-scheme-b-phase-1-revis.md)*
- build-equilibrium-snn local analysis review APPROVED: 0 blocks 7 flags. KEY PATTERNS: (1) Training loss converging to log(2)=0.6930 means network outputs near-uniform probabilities — 52% accuracy from microscopic bias, not discrimination. This is the headline finding. (2) Ablation hierarchies with n=3 folds cannot resolve differences <1pp — group into tiers. (3) t-tests on correlated experiments overstate significance. (4) Magnitude mode abstention threshold must be pre-registered or it is data snooping. (5) Sklearn models produce catastrophic Sharpe due to binary predictions = 100% turnover. (6) Fold bias (Fold 0 >> Fold 2) questions forward generalization. (7) Bootstrap CI (Script 6) is the highest priority follow-up — equilibrium claim not yet validated without it. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_171412_build-equilibrium-snn-local-analysis-rev.md)*
- Pipeline build-equilibrium-snn: completed local_analysis_code_review. APPROVED with 4 FLAGS (0 blocks). All 5 Critic FLAG corrections verified: FLAG-1 t-test corrected to p=0.303, FLAG-2 magnitude degeneration documented, FLAG-3 language to 'supported', FLAG-4 abstention confound, FLAG-5 phasic within noise. Bootstrap CI is headline finding: pooled EQ-04 vs EQ-ABL-03 = [+0.002, +0.035] excludes zero — equilibrium paradigm statistically supported. Script code correct: block bootstrap, McNemar, Cohen's d, calibration, regime analysis all verified. 4 minor FLAGS: (1) Script 5 majority/all-agree labeling bug, (2) pooled bootstrap fold boundary note, (3) summary text not updated to reflect bootstrap result, (4) structured pkl could capture more outputs. 10/10 checklist. Review at: pipeline_builds/build-equilibrium-snn_critic_analysis_code_review.md *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_183641_pipeline-build-equilibrium-snn-completed.md)*
- APPROVED with 4 FLAGS (0 blocks). All 5 Critic FLAG corrections verified: FLAG-1 t-test corrected to p=0.303, FLAG-2 magnitude degeneration documented, FLAG-3 language to 'supported', FLAG-4 abstention confound, FLAG-5 phasic within noise. Bootstrap CI is headline finding: pooled EQ-04 vs EQ-ABL-03 = [+0.002, +0.035] excludes zero — equilibrium paradigm statistically supported. Script code correct: block bootstrap, McNemar, Cohen's d, calibration, regime analysis all verified. 4 minor FLAGS: (1) Script 5 majority/all-agree labeling bug, (2) pooled bootstrap fold boundary note, (3) summary text not updated to reflect bootstrap result, (4) structured pkl could capture more outputs. 10/10 checklist. Review at: pipeline_builds/build-equilibrium-snn_critic_analysis_code_review.md | Pipeline: build-equilibrium-snn | Stage: local_analysis_code_review agent:critic pipeline:build-equilibrium-snn stage:local_analysis_code_review *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_183642_approved-with-4-flags-0-blocks-all-5-cri.md)*
- Pipeline build-equilibrium-snn: completed phase2_critic_design_review. BLOCK-1: Turnover penalty has zero gradient effect — sign(output).detach() severs gradient path, sign() has zero gradient anyway. All 4 turnover sweep experiments (P2-05..08) will produce identical models. FIX: Use differentiable output-smoothness penalty |output_t - output_{t-1}| instead. Also 6 FLAGS: (1) P2-12 duplicates P2-03, (2) fold size inequality (3-27 months), (3) clamp_weights() undefined, (4) no calibration analysis, (5) model selection ignores abstention, (6) 53% accuracy threshold ambitious given Phase 1 best of 52.6%. Review at: pipeline_builds/build-equilibrium-snn_phase2_critic_design_review.md *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_232854_pipeline-build-equilibrium-snn-completed.md)*
- BLOCKED: BLOCK-1: Turnover penalty has zero gradient effect — sign(output).detach() severs gradient path, sign() has zero gradient anyway. All 4 turnover sweep experiments (P2-05..08) will produce identical models. FIX: Use differentiable output-smoothness penalty |output_t - output_{t-1}| instead. Also 6 FLAGS: (1) P2-12 duplicates P2-03, (2) fold size inequality (3-27 months), (3) clamp_weights() undefined, (4) no calibration analysis, (5) model selection ignores abstention, (6) 53% accuracy threshold ambitious given Phase 1 best of 52.6%. Review at: pipeline_builds/build-equilibrium-snn_phase2_critic_design_review.md | Pipeline: build-equilibrium-snn | Stage: phase2_critic_design_review_blocked agent:critic pipeline:build-equilibrium-snn stage:phase2_critic_design_review_blocked *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_232855_blocked-block-1-turnover-penalty-has-zer.md)*
- Phase 2 design review for build-equilibrium-snn: BLOCKED with 1 BLOCK, 4 FLAGS. BLOCK-1 (CRITICAL): Turnover penalty in compute_loss() has zero gradient — torch.sign() is non-differentiable and .detach() makes it explicit. The 4 turnover sweep experiments (P2-05..08) would produce identical results. Recommended fix: prediction smoothness penalty (output - prev_output).pow(2) which is fully differentiable. FLAG-1: Fold 7 validation is 26 months vs 3-6 months for others (4.3x larger). FLAG-2: clamp_weights() called but not defined in class. FLAG-3: V3 baseline should specify 14-dim delta features. FLAG-4: Use macro-average for success criteria. Everything else is strong — convergence rationale is evidence-based, adaptive percentile abstention is elegant, gradient flow audit passes, experiment matrix is focused. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_232928_phase-2-design-review-for-build-equilibr.md)*
- Phase 2 revision review for build-equilibrium-snn: APPROVED 0 blocks 2 low flags. KEY PATTERN: prediction smoothness penalty (output_t - output_{t-1})^2 is the clean differentiable alternative to any loss term involving sign()/argmax()/step functions. Within TBPTT K=8, 7 active pairs get bidirectional gradient per chunk. Lambda values are K-dependent. The 11 uniform folds (from 8 heterogeneous) is the right call. Architect addressed all 5 items cleanly — revision discipline strong. Review at pipeline_builds/build-equilibrium-snn_phase2_critic_revision_review.md *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_233734_phase-2-revision-review-for-build-equili.md)*
