- # Continuous Input Mode Consistently Outperforms Spike Mode *(lessons/continuous-input-beats-spike-mode.md)*
- Across all V2 model variants (SNN and LSTM, all schemes, all sizes), passing raw Gaussian activation values (continuous mode) to the SNN outperforms Bernoulli-sampled spike trains (spike mode). *(lessons/continuous-input-beats-spike-mode.md)*
- **Implication:** For financial SNN architectures, use continuous (graded) input by default. Reserve true spiking input for neuromorphic hardware deployment where it's required. Deterministic evaluation (continuous mode) is essential for reliable metrics — stochastic eval makes all accuracy and Sharpe measurements unreliable. *(lessons/continuous-input-beats-spike-mode.md)*
- _When does this lesson apply? What should change going forward?_ *(lessons/token-ids-affect-attention-quality-not-just-count.md)*
- Spike-count readout causes dead neurons — always use membrane potential readout snn v4 gradients *(memory/entries/2026-03-17_031637_spike-count-readout-causes-dead-neurons.md)*
- V4 experiment total architecture failure: spike-count readout caused dead output neurons in >85% of 96 runs. V3 used membrane potential (continuous gradients), V4 switched to spike count (discrete, threshold-gated). Groups 5-6 magnitude: 100% abstention. Encoding comparison invalidated by output confound. V5 proposal: membrane readout fix, same matrix. 4 lessons created. v4 analysis failure *(memory/entries/2026-03-17_033432_v4-experiment-total-architecture-failure.md)*
- Major Codex Engine V2 coordinate grammar design session with Shael. Finalized dense alphanumeric as the canonical format: e0p3 e1t12 (no separator between namespace+index, spaces only between operations). Ran empirical tokenizer tests: all separators (dot, colon, slash, hyphen) cost same 16 tokens on 4-op chain; dense = 14 tokens; dense numeric = 11 tokens but bad attention signal (model fights arithmetic priors). Alphanumeric wins because token IDs (e=68, p=79, t=83) fire attention patterns associated with symbolic references/identifiers, not arithmetic. Engine mode namespace: e0=orchestrate, e1=edit, e2=create, e3=extend. Flags remain as view modifiers (camera angles) orthogonal to coordinate operations. 'Large alphanumeric model' framing coined by Shael. instance:main codex-engine v2 coordinates grammar tokenizer attention dense-mode alphanumeric *(memory/entries/2026-03-21_065733_major-codex-engine-v2-coordinate-grammar.md)*
- Legendary map (LM) concept discussed with Shael: a namespace on the main supermap where each item describes how to use coordinates. LM uses the same primitive/coordinate system it documents, creating a recursive self-describing loop. When the engine gains a new mode via e3, the LM auto-updates. Shael framed this as 'a recursive observation of your attention' — architecturally novel and compatible with transformer attention (relational cross-attention between action pattern and target). Key insight: the action IS the map, not documentation about it. Phase 3 of codex-engine-v3 will implement this. instance:main codex-engine legendary-map architecture supermap *(memory/entries/2026-03-22_215028_legendary-map-lm-concept-discussed-with.md)*
- BLOCK-1 resolved: softmax gradient at (0,0) = 0.25 (well-defined, same as sigmoid) — corrected formula, table, and framing. The 0.5-attractor problem is shared across all rate-based decodings, not a gradient singularity. FLAG-1: min_useful_rate ≈ 0.064 (not 0.02 which was guard threshold) — both reference lines added, zombie zone documented. FLAG-2: chi-sq restricted to genuine learners only (n≈10-15 with peak_lift>0.005). FLAG-3: inhibitory V5.1 extension note added. FLAG-4: reset_state() specified with fold-boundary call semantics. FLAG-5: MLP flattening note added with temporal ordering caveat. | Pipeline: v4-deep-analysis | Stage: analysis_phase2_architect_revision agent:architect pipeline:v4-deep-analysis stage:analysis_phase2_architect_revision *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-architect/memory/entries/2026-03-17_184040_block-1-resolved-softmax-gradient-at-00.md)*
