- Completed OpenClaw internals research design. Key finding: before_prompt_build plugin hook is the main leverage point for automating pipeline context injection into agent sessions. Two hook layers: internal (event scripts) and plugin (lifecycle). 5 opportunities identified: pipeline-context injection [HIGH], agent turn logging [MEDIUM], native orchestrator tool [HIGH], bootstrap file hook [MEDIUM], auto-reply commands [LOW]. Plugins run in-process with no sandbox. instance:architect pipeline:research-openclaw-internals stage:architect_design *(memory/entries/2026-03-21_033036_completed-openclaw-internals-research-de.md)*
- research-openclaw-internals design review APPROVED: 0 blocks, 3 flags. Infrastructure research doc about OpenClaw session routing, hooks, plugins. All claims verified accurate against docs. FLAG-1 (MED): lifecycle diagram conflates internal hooks and plugin hooks. FLAG-2 (LOW): registerHook vs api.on distinction unclear. FLAG-3 (LOW): workspace plugins disabled by default not mentioned as security default. Key pattern: knowledge/reference docs need different review criteria than notebook builds — accuracy, completeness, utility rather than statistical hygiene. instance:critic pipeline:research-openclaw-internals stage:critic_design_review *(memory/entries/2026-03-21_033159_research-openclaw-internals-design-revie.md)*
- Deep architectural discussion with Shael on Codex Engine V2+ direction. Key conclusions: (1) Modes should be primitives, not flags — orchestration, extend, create, edit all get their own coordinates and namespace. (2) -x extend mode is the meta-layer (lathe builds lathe) for adding new categories, custom code, namespace prefixes. (3) Plugins have presence (persist across turns, hook lifecycle) vs commands are fire-and-forget — different primitive types. (4) Temporal interaction idea: LLMs that play against time rather than humans, using SpacetimeDB for event sourcing, daemon-free via checkpointed state. (5) Persistent agent model: agents spawn with context and keep running rather than per-message cycles. New tasks created: temporal-interaction-llm-gaming, codex-engine-v2-modes-mcp-temporal. instance:main codex-engine v2 modes primitives extend-mode plugins temporal-interaction architecture *(memory/entries/2026-03-21_051420_deep-architectural-discussion-with-shael.md)*
- Major Codex Engine V2 coordinate grammar design session with Shael. Finalized dense alphanumeric as the canonical format: e0p3 e1t12 (no separator between namespace+index, spaces only between operations). Ran empirical tokenizer tests: all separators (dot, colon, slash, hyphen) cost same 16 tokens on 4-op chain; dense = 14 tokens; dense numeric = 11 tokens but bad attention signal (model fights arithmetic priors). Alphanumeric wins because token IDs (e=68, p=79, t=83) fire attention patterns associated with symbolic references/identifiers, not arithmetic. Engine mode namespace: e0=orchestrate, e1=edit, e2=create, e3=extend. Flags remain as view modifiers (camera angles) orthogonal to coordinate operations. 'Large alphanumeric model' framing coined by Shael. instance:main codex-engine v2 coordinates grammar tokenizer attention dense-mode alphanumeric *(memory/entries/2026-03-21_065733_major-codex-engine-v2-coordinate-grammar.md)*
- Codex Engine V2 and hook verification subagents dispatched at 07:28 UTC (session b9b39122). 273 messages trimmed — likely contained V2 dense alphanumeric parser implementation and before_prompt_build hook verification results. Sequencing agreed with Shael: V2 engine first, then orchestration V1 (uses improved engine), then orchestration V2. instance:main codex-engine v2 subagents hooks dispatch *(memory/entries/2026-03-21_092223_codex-engine-v2-and-hook-verification-su.md)*
- Designed temporal overlay for V2 orchestration engine: SpacetimeDB for temporal state (5 tables: pipeline_state, state_transition, handoff, agent_context, agent_presence), persistent agent context (structured cross-session memory scoped to pipeline lifecycle), autoclave shared dashboard (real-time subscriptions + time-travel queries). Key design decisions: overlay not replacement (filesystem remains source of truth, graceful degradation if SpacetimeDB unavailable), minimal V2 diff (~30 lines), Rust module for schema+reducers (~300 lines), Python client (~250 lines). New e0a coordinates for autoclave access. 5 open questions for critic including SpacetimeDB vs SQLite tradeoff. instance:architect pipeline:orchestration-engine-v2-temporal stage:architect_design *(memory/entries/2026-03-21_110558_designed-temporal-overlay-for-v2-orchest.md)*
