- build-equilibrium-snn local analysis review APPROVED: 0 blocks 7 flags. KEY PATTERNS: (1) Training loss converging to log(2)=0.6930 means network outputs near-uniform probabilities — 52% accuracy from microscopic bias, not discrimination. This is the headline finding. (2) Ablation hierarchies with n=3 folds cannot resolve differences <1pp — group into tiers. (3) t-tests on correlated experiments overstate significance. (4) Magnitude mode abstention threshold must be pre-registered or it is data snooping. (5) Sklearn models produce catastrophic Sharpe due to binary predictions = 100% turnover. (6) Fold bias (Fold 0 >> Fold 2) questions forward generalization. (7) Bootstrap CI (Script 6) is the highest priority follow-up — equilibrium claim not yet validated without it. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_171412_build-equilibrium-snn-local-analysis-rev.md)*
- Pipeline build-equilibrium-snn: completed local_analysis_critic_review. APPROVED with 5 FLAGS (0 blocks). FLAG-1 (HIGH): t-test uses per-experiment means inflating significance (p=0.040); per-fold p=0.096 NOT significant. FLAG-2 (CRITICAL): Magnitude mode positive Sharpe is artifact — models collapse to degenerate directional bias (87-100% long or 100% short by fold), identical pattern in GRU baseline. Strike 'prioritize magnitude mode' from Phase 2 recs. FLAG-3: 'VALIDATED' overstates equilibrium paradigm — consistent direction in all 3 folds but paired t-test p=0.169, awaits bootstrap CI. FLAG-4: Direction vs magnitude Sharpe comparison confounded by abstention (100% abstention forces trades vs 0-34%). FLAG-5: Phasic-only 'beats' full model by 0.10pp — within noise. Follow-up scripts well-designed, especially Script 6 (bootstrap CI). Review at: pipeline_builds/build-equilibrium-snn_critic_analysis_review.md *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_171817_pipeline-build-equilibrium-snn-completed.md)*
