- Phase 2 design review for build-equilibrium-snn: BLOCKED with 1 BLOCK, 4 FLAGS. BLOCK-1 (CRITICAL): Turnover penalty in compute_loss() has zero gradient — torch.sign() is non-differentiable and .detach() makes it explicit. The 4 turnover sweep experiments (P2-05..08) would produce identical results. Recommended fix: prediction smoothness penalty (output - prev_output).pow(2) which is fully differentiable. FLAG-1: Fold 7 validation is 26 months vs 3-6 months for others (4.3x larger). FLAG-2: clamp_weights() called but not defined in class. FLAG-3: V3 baseline should specify 14-dim delta features. FLAG-4: Use macro-average for success criteria. Everything else is strong — convergence rationale is evidence-based, adaptive percentile abstention is elegant, gradient flow audit passes, experiment matrix is focused. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_232928_phase-2-design-review-for-build-equilibr.md)*
- Phase 2 revision review for build-equilibrium-snn: APPROVED 0 blocks 2 low flags. KEY PATTERN: prediction smoothness penalty (output_t - output_{t-1})^2 is the clean differentiable alternative to any loss term involving sign()/argmax()/step functions. Within TBPTT K=8, 7 active pairs get bidirectional gradient per chunk. Lambda values are K-dependent. The 11 uniform folds (from 8 heterogeneous) is the right call. Architect addressed all 5 items cleanly — revision discipline strong. Review at pipeline_builds/build-equilibrium-snn_phase2_critic_revision_review.md *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_233734_phase-2-revision-review-for-build-equili.md)*
- Phase 2 code review for build-equilibrium-snn: APPROVED 0 blocks 5 flags. All 5 design items verified (BLOCK-1 smoothness penalty gradient ✅, 11 folds ✅, clamp_betas ✅, V3 14-dim ✅, macro-avg ✅). KEY FLAG: McNemar test pools SNN and V3 predictions that evaluate different candles (SNN starts at warmup, V3 starts at T_window+warmup) — temporal misalignment when pooled. Secondary test, doesn't affect paired t-test. Also noted: P2-03/P2-06/P2-12 are triple replicates at same config point (useful for init variance). DSR is simplified ratio not full Bailey formula. 22/22 checklist pass. Strongest notebook yet. *(/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace-critic/memory/entries/2026-03-19_235226_phase-2-code-review-for-build-equilibriu.md)*
