## Session 1b804d67 — 2026-03-20 22:27 → 2026-03-21 01:25 UTC (main)

**Topic:** Codex Engine V2 — planning, subagent dispatch, features shipped

**What happened:**
- Confirmed auto-memory extraction pipeline worked end-to-end for the first time (previous session f1efec11 → sage subagent → 4 primitives → pending_extraction.json=complete)
- Bumped subagent default timeout 5min → 10min in codex_engine.py (was cutting off verification steps)
- Planned Codex Engine V2 in 4 workstreams: 🅰 body editing, 🅱 coord cleanup, 🅲 command unification, 🅳 live diffs
- Dispatched 🅰 and 🅱 as subagents (10min timeout each)
- **🅱 landed (coord cleanup):** 4 features — archived/superseded filter, knowledge dir non-primitive filter (13→4), persona views (--as), --tag/--since filters
- **🅰 timed out** but work was done — B+, B5, B.Section all functional via F-labels; minor bug: mixed field+body returns pin
- Heartbeat ran: 2 open tasks with met deps flagged (report-to-youtube-pipeline, setup-vectorbt-nautilus-pipeline)
- Discussion: legacy command primitives (task/tasks, decisions, lessons) are redundant once engine covers them; decision to collapse
- 🅲 (command unification) and quick bug fix dispatched in remaining 36 messages (trimmed)

**Key decisions:**
- Live diffs → R-labels only (not F-labels); daemon mode with watchdog; deferred to V3
- Primitive-first gate: command creation must scaffold registry stub; primitive = source of truth
- Legacy view command primitives to be removed/collapsed

