## 2026-03-21T03:30:36Z — event ⚡⚡⚡

Completed OpenClaw internals research design. Key finding: before_prompt_build plugin hook is the main leverage point for automating pipeline context injection into agent sessions. Two hook layers: internal (event scripts) and plugin (lifecycle). 5 opportunities identified: pipeline-context injection [HIGH], agent turn logging [MEDIUM], native orchestrator tool [HIGH], bootstrap file hook [MEDIUM], auto-reply commands [LOW]. Plugins run in-process with no sandbox.

*Tags: instance:architect, pipeline:research-openclaw-internals, stage:architect_design*

*Source: session*

*Entry: `2026-03-21_033036_completed-openclaw-internals-research-de.md`*

---

## 2026-03-21T03:31:59Z — technical ⚡⚡⚡

research-openclaw-internals design review APPROVED: 0 blocks, 3 flags. Infrastructure research doc about OpenClaw session routing, hooks, plugins. All claims verified accurate against docs. FLAG-1 (MED): lifecycle diagram conflates internal hooks and plugin hooks. FLAG-2 (LOW): registerHook vs api.on distinction unclear. FLAG-3 (LOW): workspace plugins disabled by default not mentioned as security default. Key pattern: knowledge/reference docs need different review criteria than notebook builds — accuracy, completeness, utility rather than statistical hygiene.

*Tags: instance:critic, pipeline:research-openclaw-internals, stage:critic_design_review*

*Source: session*

*Entry: `2026-03-21_033159_research-openclaw-internals-design-revie.md`*

