## 2026-03-19T00:52:31Z — decision ⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡

Primitives are the universal organizational unit. Everything gets its own primitive file with YAML frontmatter: lessons/, decisions/, tasks/, projects/, pipelines/, commands/, skills/. All auto-indexed in AGENTS.md and MEMORY.md boot trees via embed_primitives.py. TOOLS.md reduced to consciousness tools + environment notes only — no more command tables or skill references (those live in their own primitive dirs). New primitives created via 'belam create <type>' which scaffolds frontmatter and triggers index rebuild. This is the workspace's fundamental design principle: if it matters, it's a primitive with a file.

*Tags: infrastructure, primitives, architecture, convention*

