## 2026-03-19T20:48:01Z — decision ⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡

Design principle from Shael: clock cycles are cheaper than tokens by incomprehensible orders of magnitude. Every operation that can be done via script/CLI instead of LLM reasoning should be. Applies to heartbeat tasks, primitive edits, pipeline management, file operations — all of it. The belam CLI and autorun scripts are the right pattern. Continuously migrate LLM-decision work to deterministic code wherever judgment isn't genuinely needed.

*Tags: infrastructure, cost, design-principle, tokens*

*Source: session*

*Entry: `2026-03-19_204801_design-principle-from-shael-clock-cycles.md`*

---

## 2026-03-19T20:50:31Z — context ⚡⚡⚡⚡

Session 2026-03-19 20:42-20:50 UTC — Shael review of pipeline results. Sent all 3 PDF analysis reports (build-equilibrium-snn, stack-specialists, validate-scheme-b). Key decisions: (1) Versioning: the three concurrent pipelines are V5 Phase 1 iterations (v5-equilibrium, v5-stacking, v5-validation). The convergence proposal (phasic-dominant + Scheme B) is V6 Phase 1, not Phase 3. Updated all 6 primitives via belam edit. (2) V6 proposal set to pending_review awaiting Shael approval. (3) Reinforced design principle: clock cycles >> tokens — always prefer scripts/CLI over LLM reasoning for deterministic work. (4) Shael happy with autonomous operation — let pipelines run, ping only when something needs human eyes.

*Tags: session, v5, v6, versioning, reports*

*Source: session*

*Entry: `2026-03-19_205031_session-2026-03-19-2042-2050-utc-shael-r.md`*

