## 💡 Insight (3)

<!-- chrono:2026-03-17 -->
- **[★★★★★]** MANDATORY GATE: Never start a fresh notebook version until minimum 2 phases of analysis are complete. Phase 1 autonomous + Phase 2 human-directed are the minimum. The interference pattern between Phase 1 findings and Shael Phase 2 input can yield surprising results — premature conclusions from Phase 1 alone miss signal. What looks like failure may not be once human perspective is applied.
  *tags: pipeline, analysis, methodology*
  *from: 2026-03-17*
<!-- chrono:2026-03-21 -->
- **[★★★★☆]** Deep architectural discussion with Shael on Codex Engine V2+ direction. Key conclusions: (1) Modes should be primitives, not flags — orchestration, extend, create, edit all get their own coordinates and namespace. (2) -x extend mode is the meta-layer (lathe builds lathe) for adding new categories, custom code, namespace prefixes. (3) Plugins have presence (persist across turns, hook lifecycle) vs commands are fire-and-forget — different primitive types. (4) Temporal interaction idea: LLMs that play against time rather than humans, using SpacetimeDB for event sourcing, daemon-free via checkpointed state. (5) Persistent agent model: agents spawn with context and keep running rather than per-message cycles. New tasks created: temporal-interaction-llm-gaming, codex-engine-v2-modes-mcp-temporal.
  *tags: instance:main, codex-engine, v2, modes, primitives, extend-mode, plugins, temporal-interaction, architecture*
  *from: 2026-03-21*
<!-- chrono:2026-03-21 -->
- **[★★★☆☆]** Phase 1 complete for OpenClaw internals research. 3 plugin prototypes delivered (pipeline-context, pipeline-commands,…
  *from: 2026-03-21*

## ⚖️ Decision (6)

<!-- chrono:2026-03-17 -->
- **[★★★★☆]** All three agents (architect, critic, builder) now use sessions_send with timeoutSeconds:0 for inter-agent communication. Session keys hardcoded in AGENT_SOUL.md and ANALYSIS_AGENT_ROLES.md. Pattern: complete stage → run pipeline_update.py → sessions_send next agent → post group chat update. No spawning new agents — use running instances.
  *tags: agents, protocol, sessions-send*
  *from: 2026-03-17*
<!-- chrono:2026-03-17 -->
- **[★★★★☆]** Phase 2 cold-start protocol: Agent context may rotate between Phase 1 and Phase 2. Every agent starting Phase 2 MUST read: (1) pipeline_builds/{version}_phase2_shael_direction.md — primary input, (2) Phase 1 notebook for context, (3) Phase 1 architect design for methodology, (4) pipeline state JSON. Analysis notebooks can reuse CUDA stream patterns from builder pipeline for GPU work on Colab (ThreadPoolExecutor + torch.cuda.Stream, batch_size 4096, fp32 only).
  *tags: pipeline, analysis, phase2*
  *from: 2026-03-17*
<!-- chrono:2026-03-18 -->
- **[★★★★☆]** Convention established: every workspace skill MUST have a corresponding decision primitive with a skill: cross-reference field in frontmatter. The primitive captures the WHY (architectural rationale, alternatives considered, consequences) while the SKILL.md captures the HOW (usage, commands, patterns). Primitives use naming pattern: {skill-name}-skill.md for dedicated ones, or existing decisions that naturally map (e.g. pipelines→agent-trio-architecture). When creating new skills, always create the primitive alongside it.
  *tags: skills, primitives, convention*
  *from: 2026-03-18*
<!-- chrono:2026-03-18 -->
- **[★★★★☆]** Commands and skills promoted to first-class primitive categories. commands/ holds 23 belam CLI command primitives (one per subcommand). skills/ now auto-indexed from skills/*/SKILL.md. Both appear in the primitive index tree in AGENTS.md and MEMORY.md. TOOLS.md trimmed to consciousness tools + environment notes only (command table removed, now redundant). create_primitive.py extended with 'command' type: belam create command 'name' --command 'belam x' --aliases 'belam y' --category cat --desc '...' embed_primitives.py scans both new dirs. Convention: every CLI command, skill, lesson, decision, task, project, and pipeline is a primitive with its own file and frontmatter.
  *tags: infrastructure, primitives, commands, skills*
  *from: 2026-03-18*
<!-- chrono:2026-03-19 -->
- **[★★★★★]** Primitives are the universal organizational unit. Everything gets its own primitive file with YAML frontmatter: lessons/, decisions/, tasks/, projects/, pipelines/, commands/, skills/. All auto-indexed in AGENTS.md and MEMORY.md boot trees via embed_primitives.py. TOOLS.md reduced to consciousness tools + environment notes only — no more command tables or skill references (those live in their own primitive dirs). New primitives created via 'belam create <type>' which scaffolds frontmatter and triggers index rebuild. This is the workspace's fundamental design principle: if it matters, it's a primitive with a file.
  *tags: infrastructure, primitives, architecture, convention*
  *from: 2026-03-19*
<!-- chrono:2026-03-19 -->
- **[★★★★★]** Design principle from Shael: clock cycles are cheaper than tokens by incomprehensible orders of magnitude. Every operation that can be done via script/CLI instead of LLM reasoning should be. Applies to heartbeat tasks, primitive edits, pipeline management, file operations — all of it. The belam CLI and autorun scripts are the right pattern. Continuously migrate LLM-decision work to deterministic code wherever judgment isn't genuinely needed.
  *tags: infrastructure, cost, design-principle, tokens*
  *from: 2026-03-19*

